## 🛠️ Setup Instructions

### 1. Clone the Repository

```bash
git clone https://github.com/uitmhilmi/return-refund-system.git
cd return-refund-system
```

### 2. Import the Project

Open the project in your IDE (e.g., NetBeans):

- File > Open Project > Select the folder
- Ensure Java version and Tomcat server are configured

### 3. Setup the Database

- Create a database (e.g., `return_refund_system`)
- Run the provided SQL script (if available) to create tables
- Update your DB credentials in your DAO or `DatabaseConnection.java`

```java
String jdbcURL = "jdbc:mysql://localhost:3307/return_refund_system";
String dbUser = "appuser";
String dbPassword = "";
```

### 4. Deploy and Run

- Right-click the project > Run
- Access the app in your browser:
  ```
  http://localhost:8080/ReturnRefundSystem-1.0/
  ```

